node.text:
Flying into Kathmandu is a thrill! The airport is surrounded by terrain and high mountains. The approach is steep, with fast changing weather into play. It is captain’s landing only. Watch how @gonationalair B747 cargo plane land there to bringing in medical aid supplies.

External footage by @flight_101_ @ktmspotter 

#samchui #samchuiphotos #gonationalair #nationalairlines #Boeing747 #B747 #kathmandu #tribhuvaninternationalairport #landing #avgeek #aviation

node.title: A special B747 landing at Kathmandu

node.text:
Watch this spectacular flypass to celebrate @qantas 100th birthday! 
Sydney has commemorated Qantas 100-year anniversary by lighting up its iconic Sydney Harbour Bridge as a larger-than-life birthday cake complete with illuminated candles that were blown out by a Qantas 787 as it did a low level overfly at 1,500 feet.

More than 1,300 LED tubes, 126 LED fixtures and 38 searchlights lit up the full expanse of the world’s most famous bridge in the ultimate tribute from Sydney, the city which has been home to Qantas for more than eight decades.
 
200 passengers, including 100 Qantas staff, were on board the 100-minute flight which was a special Centenary Scenic Flight to mark the airline’s 100th year. ✈️ (Footage: Qantas)
.
.

node.text:
PPL checkride PASSED! 😃

I was so stressed out in the past days, only managed to sleep 3 hours and go to the exam at 7am this morning. With some good luck, persistency and hard study, it paid off! It certainly don’t look as easy as people say. The hard work behind every pilot don’t get mentioned often. I will be making a vlog documenting my entire journey here soon.

I would like to thank my CFI instructor @tex_zane and all the support from fellow pilots at @slingpilotacademy You all gave me the best support I can ever ask for!

Ok who will be my next passenger? 😁✈️🧋

Thanks to @caffeinated_adventurer for the sweet card and gift.

Weekend vlog is out! I was on a humanitarian mission inside a @gonationalair B747-400BCF delivering medical cargo aids. I flew from Frankfurt Hahn to Islamabad, Pakistan and over the Himalayas to Kathmandu, Nepal. The flight originated from the USA carrying nearly 80 tons of USAid destined for Pakistan and Nepal.

Our B747 landing into Kathmandu was a thriller! After passing through the last clouds, the entire Kathmandu valley came into sight. Our descend was much steeper than the usual 3 degrees glideslope and require all the breaks to come to a full stop at the end of the runway in Kathmandu due to high altitude.

What a great privilege to be part of the team to send these much-needed supplies around the world and document behind the scenes of such a mission! I felt like “an airplane man” stayed inside the B747 for 40 hours from dark to light to dark again! That’s just 2 days in the shoes of charter cargo crew life! Certainly very different to the passenger airlines. Full video is on YouTube.✈️

Thanks to @ktmspotter for external footage of landing/takeoff at KTM
